[thinking] I'm contemplating the visibility of top-level classes in Scala and whether they can compile publicly. I wonder if non-public declaring classes are even possible or if a Scala private class can exist. What about using private[package]? I’m thinking Modifier.isPublic might return false in certain cases. It could be that methods from a subclass are public. I need to inspect the MemberUtils class to fully understand its role in checking accessibilities.
[thinking] 
