ll also need to ensure there's a public interface for Scala access. It looks like a top-level public holder class could be the best solution for nested types.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining Nested Class Access**\\n\\nI'm thinking about a nested static class without a public modifier, which means `Modifier.isPublic` is false. It implements a public nested interface, but I wonder if Scala can still reference `MethodUtilsAccessTargets.PackagePrivateGreeting`. Because it's package-private, it might not be accessible unless it's public. If it's in the same package, that could work. I could avoid referencing the type directly and use public factory methods that return an Object or interface/base, and then get the class by using `target.getClass`.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_1ZPpNlnJLUV3JPIDBlFl7wiA|fc_03a0e1975ef686520169fd676d10788197be3d52874052d5f0", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.playframework/play_3/3.0.0/src/test/java/org_playframework/play_3/MethodUtilsAccessTargets.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_playframework.play_3;\n\npublic final class MethodUtilsAccessTargets {\n    private MethodUtilsAccessTargets() {\n    }\n\n    public interface Greeting {\n        String greet(String name);\n    }\n\n    public static class Base {\n        public String inheritedEcho(String value) {\n            return \"base:\" + value;\n        }\n    }\n\n    static final class PackagePrivateGreeting implements Greeting {\n        @Override\n        public String greet(String name) {\n            return \"hello \" + name;\n        }\n    }\n\n    static final class PackagePrivateOverride extends Base {\n        @Override\n        public String inheritedEcho(String value) {\n            return \"child:\" + value;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static Greeting greeting() {\n        return new PackagePrivateGreeting();\n    }\n\n    public static Base overrideTarget() {\n        return new PackagePrivateOverride();\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2927, "output": 1868, "cacheRead": 28160, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32955, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778214738554, "responseId": "resp_03a0e1975ef686520169fd6754e78481979f839de2e91730dd"}}
